    <bioghist encodinganalog="545">
      <head>Biographical History</head>
      <p>Francesco Sapori (1890-1964) was a university professor in Italy and the author of books and critical works on art.  In 
	  addition he wrote poetry, novels and religious books.</p>
    </bioghist>
    <scopecontent encodinganalog="520">
      <head>Scope and Contents of the Collection</head>
      <p>The <emph render="bold">Francesco Sapori Papers</emph> consist of <emph render="bold">Writings</emph> (articles, books, pamphlets etc. on such topics as art, literature, history and 
	  the Bible), <emph render="bold">Printed material</emph> (books that mention the author, and other books, magazines, clippings 
	  and pamphlets), and <emph render="bold">Memorabilia</emph> (photographs, scrapbooks, etc.).</p>
    </scopecontent>
    <arrangement encodinganalog="351$a">
      <head>Arrangement of the Collection</head>
      <p>Material is in alphabetical order.</p>
    </arrangement>
